body:
So... while digging in the Current Refinements code, I noticed several unused (and most likely broken?) features that [we document in the connector](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/current-refinements/js/#create-a-render-function). I'm still confused by what API we want so I might be wrong.

Top-level `refine` and `createURL` were never used. I think they should only exist in the items' refinements themselves:

```ts
export type ConnectorRefinement = {
  attribute: string;
  type: string;
  value: string | number;
  label: string;
  operator?: string;
  count?: number;
  exhaustive?: boolean;
};

export type Item = {
  attribute: string;
  label: string;
  refinements: ItemRefinement[];
  refine(refinement: ItemRefinement): void;
  createURL(state: ItemRefinement): string;
};
```

These were not tested so I took the opportunity to at least cover basic cases.

I think we're now on the right track to implement the scoped results inside Current Refinements.

---

**EDIT**

I reverted the changes on `refine` and `createURL` for now to not make a rushed decision.
